Three stories, two settings, two answers.
In the contemporary one, the anthros are humans with animal genetics that formed over generations and turned them into anthros that are mostly human in shape, and thus can wear human shoes (but it’s uncomfortable for many) but generally have shoes designed for them as their middle toes are longer compared to the outer ones (and all clawed). The other setting has digitigrade feet for the anthro races. Some wear specialty designed boots, others armoured sandals, some wear basic foot wraps and others go without.
